cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CS, cs.SD, cs.CL 

This paper involves data exploration and analysis of a large dataset of online petitions, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper focuses on the use of social media campaigning in relation to the success of petitions. The paper also involves data processing and analysis, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.CS (Computational Science), and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper uses language detection and named-entity recognition, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
